---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';
const updated = 'July 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — SNAG" description="How SNAG and Docunation collect, use and protect your information.">
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-ink">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-3">Last updated {updated} · <em>Draft — pending legal review</em></p>

    <div class="prose-custom mt-8 space-y-6 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-2">
      <p>
        This policy explains how {SITE.company} ("we", "us") handles personal
        information collected through the SNAG mobile application and this
        website, in accordance with the New Zealand Privacy Act 2020 and the
        Australian Privacy Act 1988.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">What we collect</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Account information:</strong> your name, email address, and the
        organisation(s) you belong to. <strong>Report content:</strong> photos,
        descriptions, comments, and investigation records your team creates in
        SNAG. <strong>Website enquiries:</strong> details you submit through our
        contact form. <strong>Usage data:</strong> privacy-respecting, aggregate
        analytics about how the website is used (no cross-site tracking).
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">How we use it</h2>
      <p>
        To operate the service (routing reports to the right people in your
        organisation, sending notification emails you'd expect, keeping audit
        trails your organisation relies on), to respond to enquiries, and to
        improve the product. We do not sell personal information.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">Who can see report data</h2>
      <p>
        Report content belongs to the organisation it was reported into and is
        visible only to that organisation's members, according to their role
        and site access. Public submissions are visible to the receiving
        organisation and to the person who submitted them.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">Storage and security</h2>
      <p>
        Data is stored with our cloud infrastructure provider in the
        Asia-Pacific region, protected by row-level access controls,
        encrypted in transit, with photos held in private, permission-scoped
        storage.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal
        information at any time by contacting us at {SITE.contactEmail}. If you
        are in New Zealand you may complain to the Office of the Privacy
        Commissioner; in Australia, to the OAIC.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-ink">Contact</h2>
      <p>{SITE.company} · {SITE.contactEmail}</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
